  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    SubGraph<E extends Vertex<E>>
    Subgraph is a graph, where each vertex of it corresponds to particular vertex of parent graph.
    SubGraphFactory
    Factory useful for instantiating specific subgraphs such as spanning tree.

    Vertex of subgraph.
    SubGraphView<T extends Vertex<T>,U extends Graph<T>,V extends GraphView<U,T>>
    Representation of subgraph, which can be painted on java.awt.Graphic2D object.
